 href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923312\">2.4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the event of a network services provider outage&nbsp; 26</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923313\">2.5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the event of a flooding or water Leakage&nbsp; 26</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923314\">2.6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the event of Burglary/Office Break-in&nbsp; 27</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923315\">2.7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the event of Computer failure, hacking or virus invasion&nbsp; 27</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923316\">3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BCP Review, Testing and Implementation&nbsp;&nbsp; 28</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923317\">3.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BCP Testing&nbsp; 28</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923318\">3.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BCP Implementation&nbsp; 28</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923319\">4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Disaster Incident Management Process: 29</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923320\">4.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recovery Plan checklists (To be Filled in the Event of a Disaster) 29</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923321\">4.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Notification of incident 29</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923322\">4.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Upon declaration of Disaster: 30</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923323\">4.4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business Recovery Phase (72 hours - full recovery) 31</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923324\">4.5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Secure funding for relocation&nbsp; 31</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923325\">4.6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Operations recovered&nbsp; 32</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923326\">SECTION 3: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;MIS Disaster Recovery Procedures&nbsp;&nbsp; 33</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923327\">1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Introduction&nbsp;&nbsp; 33</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923328\">1.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scenario: Loss of power for 2 hours to 1 day&nbsp; 33</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923329\">1.1.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Description&nbsp; 33</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923330\">1.1.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recovery Steps- Inverter 33</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923331\">1.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scenario 2- loss of power for 1 day or longer&nbsp; 34</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923332\">1.2.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Description&nbsp; 34</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923333\">1.2.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recovery Steps- Inverter 34</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923334\">1.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scenario 3 &ndash;Failure of backup power supply&nbsp; 35</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923335\">1.3.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recovery Steps- Inverter 35</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923336\">1.4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scenario 3- Server failure&nbsp; 35</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923337\">1.4.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Description&nbsp; 35</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923338\">1.4.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Single workstation&nbsp; 35</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923339\">1.4.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Entire Local Area Network at the branch&nbsp; 36</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923340\">1.4.4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Wide Area Network (WAN) 36</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923341\">1.4.5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Head Office Data Centre&nbsp; 36</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923342\">1.5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scenario 5- Loss of building&nbsp; 37</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923343\">1.5.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Description&nbsp; 37</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923344\">1.5.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recovery Steps&nbsp; 37</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923345\">Appendices&nbsp;&nbsp; 38</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923346\">1.6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Appendix A: Disaster Management Team (DMT) 38</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923347\">1.7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Appendix B: Disaster Response Coordinators (DRC) 38</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923348\">1.8&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Appendix C: Disaster Recovery Team (DRT) Members&nbsp; 38</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923349\">1.9&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Appendix D: Emergency numbers&nbsp; 41</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923350\">1.10&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Appendix E: Emergency Assembly Points/Locations&nbsp; 42</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923351\">1.11&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Appendix F: Minimum acceptable recovery Requirements&nbsp; 42</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923352\">1.12&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Appendix G: Forms&nbsp; 43</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923353\">1.12.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Incident/Disaster form&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 43</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923354\">1.12.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Critical equipment status form&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 45</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://documents.musoni.co.ke/wp-admin/post.php?post=19&amp;action=edit#_Toc424923355\">1.13&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Appendix H: Building Evacuation Information&nbsp; 46</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h1><a name=\"_Toc424923265\"></a>SECTION 1: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BUSINESS IMPACT ASSESSMENT</h1>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc424923266\"></a>1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Introduction</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc424923267\"></a><a name=\"_Toc403753609\"></a>1.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Objectives</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Musoni Kenya ltd head office is housed on a single floor of a building; however, the branches are geographically spread and operate independently which is normal for the institution of our type. It is therefore important that management provides a clear vision, leadership and a commitment to resources to ensure recovery and continuity of operations for each branch and head office. Successful future recovery efforts will depend on planning and coordination activities that must take place well in advance of actual disaster situations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The main objective of the business impact assessment is to:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Identify the critical business functions/departments, business unit processes and the estimated Recovery Time Objective (RTO) for each.</li>\r\n	<li>Estimate the financial, customer/operational and or legal / regulatory impacts in case a department/business unit fails to operate, assuming a worst case scenario.</li>\r\n	<li>Determine the estimated number of personnel required for recovery operations.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide a foundation for implementing Business Resumption, Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery Plans.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc424923268\"></a><a name=\"_Toc403753610\"></a>1.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scope</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Business Impact Analysis (BIA) attempts to cover all the business units of Musoni Kenya Ltd i.e. Operations, Credit Administration, Finance&amp; Administration, IT, Internal Audit, Risk and Human Resources. It is the critical initial step in contingency management within the institution and will allow identification of system restoration requirements and the order of restoration of services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The scope for the Musoni Kenya Ltd BIA includes the following business units and shared services:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Finance &amp; Administration</li>\r\n	<li>Operations</li>\r\n	<li>Credit Administration</li>\r\n	<li>Human Resources</li>\r\n	<li>Internal Audit</li>\r\n	<li>Information Technology (IT)</li>\r\n	<li>Risk</li>\r\n	<li>Branches</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc424923269\"></a><a name=\"_Toc403753611\"></a>1.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Approach</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We held discussions with each department head. The main objective of the discussions was to identify activities, processes, potential incidences along with associated acceptable recovery time frames, estimated financial &amp; operational impacts and estimated resources &amp;personnel required for recovery operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc424923270\"></a><a name=\"_Toc403753612\"></a>1.4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document Organisation</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The summarised business activities provided by each department during the discussions is presented in the next section. The last section, Business Impact Summary includes information that is considered most appropriate in the overall institution perspective to assist in the development of an appropriate business continuity and recovery strategy such as the recovery personnel requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc424923271\"></a><a name=\"_Toc403753613\"></a>2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Summary of Findings<a name=\"_Toc403753614\"></a></h1>\r\n\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc424923272\"></a>2.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Departmental Business Processes and Documents</h2>\r\n\r\n<table style=\"width:637px\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Business Processes</strong></td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Description</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Documents &amp; Resources</strong></td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Document Source/</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>alternative</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"5\"><strong>Department:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Finance &amp; Administration</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Reporting</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Internal monthly, quarterly and annual reporting to shareholders and management, financial partners, statutory bodies.</td>\r\n			<td>Financial reports liquidity &amp; board meetings</td>\r\n			<td>Hardcopy and soft copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Company budget 5yr plan</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Management of process; analysis of variances between budgeted and actual results.</td>\r\n			<td>Approved budget</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copy of budget and Microfin system</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Statutory submissions and reporting</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Statutory (KRA, NSSF, NHIF etc.) monthly and annual submissions and reporting</td>\r\n			<td>Tax returns, Permits, Tax compliance certificates</td>\r\n			<td>Online submissions and hard copies of monthly returns</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Finance/ accounting</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Provide financial/ accounting services, posting entries in ACCPAC</td>\r\n			<td>Financial statements</td>\r\n			<td>Bank reconciliations and audited financial reports soft, online and hard copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Payroll preparation</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Prepare payroll, process approval and post salaries on all staff accounts</td>\r\n			<td>Payroll &amp; payslips</td>\r\n			<td>Payroll summaries soft and hard copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Payment to suppliers and service providers</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Prepare EFTs Post payments on vendors and service providers&rsquo; accounts or post cheques.</td>\r\n			<td>Invoices, payment vouchers, LPOs, cheque books</td>\r\n			<td>Hard copies of supplier invoices slips, payment vouchers and cheque books</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Funding/ liquidity management</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Ensure that the company has enough funds in both bank and M-PESA accounts to run the business.</td>\r\n			<td>Weekly liquidity reports</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copies and online access.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Assets and liabilities management</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Monitor all company assets (fixed assets) and liabilities to ensure that company assets fall within the required benchmarks and standards.</td>\r\n			<td>Fixed assets register</td>\r\n			<td>Centralized fixed assets register</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"5\"><strong>Department:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Administration</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Negotiate for and purchase goods and services</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Source for, negotiate with vendors and place orders for goods and services.</td>\r\n			<td>Procurement records; files and minutes.</td>\r\n			<td>Approved quotations and signed contracts both hard copy</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Maintain the contract system and records</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Update file contracts.</td>\r\n			<td>Profiles of pre-qualified service providers and suppliers, contract awards and performance monitoring reports</td>\r\n			<td>Signed contracts hard copy.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Generate LPOs</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Follow through the process of writing, generating, approval and dispatching of LPOs</td>\r\n			<td>LPO Book</td>\r\n			<td>Hard copies of LPOs, services providers contracts</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Insurance requirements</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Identify insurance needs (credit life, medical, asset, etc.), alternative risk financing, place coverage.</td>\r\n			<td>MoUs &amp; SLAs</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Hard &amp; soft copies.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>services providers</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"5\"><strong>Department:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Credit</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Client group formation &amp; training</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Identify potential group members and carry out preliminary appraisal / investigations. Qualifying group members are trained in group procedures, financial literacy, etc. Introduce them to MUSONI Microfinance Ltd&rsquo;s products and services.</td>\r\n			<td>Group training &amp; management manual</td>\r\n			<td>Hard &amp; soft copies. Back up</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Group Registration</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">WCOs complete Prospective group electronic forms on tablet and synchronize them to Musoni MIS. CSA validates the client data and BM approves.</td>\r\n			<td>Client Registration application on Tablet</td>\r\n			<td>Group Registration application on portal and hard copy registration forms.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Group management</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<p>Electing group members, formulating the group constitution, completing client registration app forms and capturing the clients&rsquo; including the meeting day, time and venue.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Conduct weekly, fortnightly and/or monthly group meetings, recording of minutes, signing of attendance registers, receiving loan applications, disbursements, and repayments and enforcing co-guarantee mechanism.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Group training &nbsp;manual</td>\r\n			<td>Hard &amp;soft copies. Group minutes, Client forum reports.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Client Registration</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">WCOs complete Prospective client&rsquo;s electronic forms and synchronize them to Musoni server. CSA validates the client data and BM approves</td>\r\n			<td>Client Registration application on Tablet</td>\r\n			<td>Client Registration application on portal and hard copy registration forms.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Loan Appraisal forms (Site Visit Forms)</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">WCO fills the electronic form on tablet, synchronize to MIS. Branch Managers reviews and during branch credit committee. Analyse the credibility of the customer - cash flows, securities, character, etc. Check for completeness of information provided and validity.</td>\r\n			<td>Home and business visit application form on tablet</td>\r\n			<td>Home and business visit on web portal and hard copy forms available in branch store.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Loan approval</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Credit committee interface used in Presentation of the loan file to the respective credit committees, both hard copy and soft copy information as captured in the system. Ensure security perfection (caveat and mortgage fees are duly paid</td>\r\n			<td>Credit committee interface</td>\r\n			<td>Hard copy loan application file, MIS. Credit Committee storage</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Loan monitoring</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Analysing reports (arrears, PAR, disbursements, expected repayments, etc.) on a daily, weekly and monthly basis. Field visitation, telephone calls to clients, submission.</td>\r\n			<td>Loan monitoring reports including branch portfolio, WCO and group.&nbsp;&nbsp; (PAR, repayments, arrears, payments due, etc).</td>\r\n			<td>Hard &amp; soft copy. Originals generated from Branch.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Loan repayments</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Monitor group and client reports as generated by MIS after clients have sent their payments.</td>\r\n			<td>Jasper client reports, Mpesa receipts and statement</td>\r\n			<td>Client pass books, Mpesa statement</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Delinquency management</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Analysing arrears reports, client follow up through telephone calls, field visitation, demand letters, recalling the loans and following the due process for recovering the credit facility.</td>\r\n			<td>Arrears reports, Branch portfolio report, WCO performance reports</td>\r\n			<td>SAM report, MIS</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Loan write-off</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Using Loan provisioning report, write off request forms prepared for loans in arrears over 120 days, seek Write off committee approval to write-off the loans from active portfolio.</td>\r\n			<td>Arrears reports, Loan provisioning reports, Write off report</td>\r\n			<td>MIS and write off files.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Security Management</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Receipt, validate, perfect, store, monitor and retrieval of loan securities.</td>\r\n			<td>Land titles, vehicle log books, and chattel mortgage deeds &amp; securities register and kept under dual controlled safe.</td>\r\n			<td>Hard copy (physical) original &amp; photocopies of security documents Ministry of lands &amp; KRA</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"5\"><strong>Department:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Human Resource</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Recruitment and Selection</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Carry out a manpower plan to identify gaps and future needs</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Advertise for the position</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Application screening</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Interview process</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Reference checks/background checks</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Appointment of candidate</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Employee requisition form.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Job applications and CVs</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Personnel files</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copies and hard copies.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Performance Management</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Bi annual performance appraisals</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Performance Improvement Program for underperforming staff.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Appraisal forms.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>PIP templates</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copies and hard copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Payroll</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Monthly payroll changes on joiners and leavers.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Advise Finance to effect the above changes on the payroll.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Documentation of staff payroll records in personnel files.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Annual salary benchmarking with peer institutions.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Employee contract document</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>PIN</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>NSSF</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>NHIF</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Hard copies found in personnel files</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Training and Development</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Carry out a training needs assessment</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Develop an annual training calendar</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Coordinate and deliver training</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Evaluate training outcome</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Training calendar</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Training slides and other materials.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Feedback forms</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Register of training done</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copies and hard copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Motivation, Reward &amp; Benefits Administration.</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quarterly hall of fame to appreciate exceptional performers.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>WCO, SWCO, BM &amp; CSA performance based bonus scheme.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Competitive internal promotions</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Medical Cover administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Pension administration</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Internal staff loans &amp; Standard Chartered MOU.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Staff welfare kitty / committee to address welfare matters</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Occasional team building sessions.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>End of year parties.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Hall of fame template</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Bonus parameters</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Medical cover application forms.(work closely with Trustmark Brokers)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Pension application forms and policy documents.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Welfare application form (approved by the welfare committee).</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Hard copies and soft copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Employee Feedback</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Regular employee surveys to identify concerns.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Grievance procedure</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Open forums with staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Questionnaires.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Msurvey Contract document</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Hard copies and soft copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Staff Exit &amp; Separation</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Disciplinary procedure and committee</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Performance review committee and PIP records for poor performing employees.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Voluntary resignations</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Handing over process and clearance</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Advise Finance to pay final dues</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Employee handbook (Disciplinary Code).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Minutes of committee meetings.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Resignation acceptance letters</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Termination or dismissal letters</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Exit form and handing over documents.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copies and hard copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\"><strong>Department:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Internal Audit</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Internal audit strategy</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Define audit objectives and universe for a 3 year period</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Define audit responsibilities and independence</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Align audit objectives to Musoni needs</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Determine auditable entities and resources available</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Approved Internal audit strategic plan</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Approved Internal audit charter</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Hard copy and soft copy backup</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Risk-based Audit Planning</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Identify key risks</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Define audit universe and select the module for audit activities</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Establish the key objectives</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Schedule audit resources</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Validate the scope for audit</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Approved Annual Risk-based Audit plan</td>\r\n			<td>Hard copy and soft copy backup.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Field work</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Entrance meetings and client engagement and notification,</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Understanding the policies and procedures,</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Execution of the internal audit- (collect data, prepare working schedules, conduct audit tests, assess controls</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Conduct Exit meeting</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Supervisory reviews</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Supervisory review notes</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Internal audit manual</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Internal Audit Programs</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Internal audit excel working papers (For audit tests)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Internal work plans</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Audit reporting</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Drafting reporting</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Final discussions with management&nbsp; responses,</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Circulation of all final reports to stakeholders</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Draft Reports</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Final reports with management responses</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Follow-up Audits</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Prepare status for implementation for previous quarter issues raised and conduct sample audit tests to confirm implementation</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Closure of items implemented</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Implementation status for the previous period audit findings and external management letters</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Audit investigations</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Receive audit allegation/ requests for investigation from management</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Analyze the matter</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Determine the risk</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Perform the investigation</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Fact finding</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Conduct interviews and obtain audit evidence.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Finalize reports for management action</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Special investigation reports</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Copies of documentary evidences</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Scanned copies of evidences</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copies and hardcopy backups</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Audit Committee meetings</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Quarterly meetings discussions</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Agenda</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minutes</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Matters arising</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Standing items</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Any other business</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>Audit committee board papers</td>\r\n			<td>Soft copies circulated and filed</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"5\"><strong>Department:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Musoni core operating system</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Management of the banking system that provides the interface for processing Credit, Savings and integrated chart of accounts.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The 1st&amp; 2nd&nbsp;level support maintained at the head office. 3nd&nbsp;level support maintained by Musoni Services, the vendor.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>The entire database system is hosted and managed by Musoni services.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Back up database to be established locally</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>SLAs (internal &amp; external), system administration manuals, Original installation and setup CDs/ DVDs for OS &amp; applications.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>System configurations</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Hard &amp; soft copiesBack up/ Suppliers/Service providers</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>OEM Installation software media and backups</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Safaricom &ndash; M-Pesa</td>\r\n			<td>Management of the M-Pesa system&nbsp; that is used to receive and send funds from and to clients respectively</td>\r\n			<td>SLAs</td>\r\n			<td>Hard &amp; soft copies</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Service desk system</td>\r\n			<td>System used to track and manage all issues registered by users.</td>\r\n			<td>SLA, system management (installation and configuration) manuals,</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Hard and soft copies.back up/ suppliers/ service providers</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Installation media and backups.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Wide Area Network WAN &amp; Local Area Networks (LANs)</td>\r\n			<td>Manage the WAN &amp; LANs, monitoring of WAN availability and performance, monitors devices on the LAN &amp; WAN.</td>\r\n			<td>PRTG network monitor, network equipment (switches &amp; routers) and servers</td>\r\n			<td>Backups (software, configurations, etc).</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">E-mail System</td>\r\n			<td>Set-up and management of the company email system.</td>\r\n			<td>Server (hardware &amp; software) and system configurations.</td>\r\n			<td>Backups &ndash; OEM software media, hard and soft copy configurations.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Primary and secondary data centres</td>\r\n			<td>Maintain both the primary and secondary data centres. PDC, database (Musoni system and email), DNS, DHCP and backups all setup and replicated at both sites.</td>\r\n			<td>System configurations, OEM installation media, SLAs &ndash; equipment maintenance.</td>\r\n			<td>Hard &amp; soft copy backups, OEM media backups.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">IT assets inventory</td>\r\n			<td>Maintain all IT assets such as computers, laptops, tablets , mobile lines, printers and&nbsp; accessories</td>\r\n			<td>Assets register</td>\r\n			<td>Hard &amp; Soft copy Backups</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Standard Operating Environment (SoE)</td>\r\n			<td>Maintain common operating procedures within the ICT system and standard configurations.</td>\r\n			<td>SoE report</td>\r\n			<td>Hard copy &amp; soft copy,.back up</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"5\"><strong>Department:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Risk &amp; Compliance</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Risk identification and profiling</td>\r\n			<td>Identify inherent, new, internal and external risks. Work with different each respective department to get solutions to the identified risks and mitigate the risks too.</td>\r\n			<td>Risk registers</td>\r\n			<td>Hard &amp; soft copies. Back up</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Compliance Checks and assessment</td>\r\n			<td>Run compliance checks on our activities vis a vis policies and procedures</td>\r\n			<td>Compliance monitoring tools</td>\r\n			<td>Hard &amp; soft copies Back up</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">Reporting</td>\r\n			<td>Produce internal risk and compliance reports, follow-up implementation to ensure that corrective action is taken.</td>\r\n			<td>Risk &amp; Compliance reports</td>\r\n			<td>Hard &amp; soft copies. Back up</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc424923273\"></a><a name=\"_Toc403753615\"></a>2.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business Impact Assessment</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Through the discussions, we were able to establish the impact of disaster on business if any of the business units is unable to operate normally. The impact value is an indication of the severity of the impact to the company that would result if the department were unable to function. The matrix below shows how a disaster in any of the business units would impact on the listed business parameters. Business impact is rated on a scale of 0-4, where 0 = no impact and 4 = severe impact</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Business Impact</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Finance &amp; Admin.</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Operations</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Credit Admin.</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Human Resource</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Internal Audit</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>IT</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Risk</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Branch Operations</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Overall Impact rating</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Increased operational cost</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td><strong>17</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Cash Flow</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td><strong>13</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Competitive Advantage</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td><strong>23</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Shareholder Confidence</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td><strong>20</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Financial Reporting</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td><strong>11</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Institutional Image</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td><strong>23</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Employee Morale</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td><strong>17</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Customer Service</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td><strong>24</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Employee Resignations</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td><strong>8</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Vendor Relations</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td><strong>5</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Regulatory</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td><strong>12</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Increases in Liability</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td><strong>5</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Overall Impact rating</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>38</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>28</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>24</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>18</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>10</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>33</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>10</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>17</strong></td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The table above reveals that in case of disaster:-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Finance department, IT, Operations and Credit Admin. will have the biggest impact on the business of the institution. In the business continuity planning process, these departments and functions should be given priority.</li>\r\n	<li>Customer Service, the institution&rsquo;s image &amp; competitive advantage and shareholder confidence would be the most affected areas.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc424923274\"></a><a name=\"_Toc403753616\"></a>2.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Critical Business Records &amp; Documents for each Department</h2>\r\n\r\n<table style=\"width:631px\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Department</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Record Name</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>When Required</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Media Type</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Alternate Source</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"7\"><strong>Finance Dept.</strong></td>\r\n			<td>Approved budget</td>\r\n			<td>Annually</td>\r\n			<td>PCs and files</td>\r\n			<td>Back-ups</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Tax returns and Tax compliance certificates</td>\r\n			<td>Monthly</td>\r\n			<td>PCs and files</td>\r\n			<td>Back-ups, KRA website</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Payroll</td>\r\n			<td>Monthly</td>\r\n			<td>PCs and files</td>\r\n			<td>Back-ups, partners</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Invoices and Payment vouchers</td>\r\n			<td>Daily</td>\r\n			<td>PCs and files</td>\r\n			<td>Partners</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Liquidity reports</td>\r\n			<td>Daily</td>\r\n			<td>PCs and files</td>\r\n			<td>Back-ups</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Fixed assets register</td>\r\n			<td>Monthly</td>\r\n			<td>PCs and files</td>\r\n			<td>Back-ups</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Contracts with service providers</td>\r\n			<td>When needed</td>\r\n			<td>PCs and files</td>\r\n			<td>Back-ups, Partners</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Operations</strong></td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"4\"><strong>Credit</strong></td>\r\n			<td>Group training manual</td>\r\n			<td>Daily</td>\r\n			<td>PCs and files</td>\r\n			<td>Back-ups</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>System generated portfolio reports</td>\r\n			<td>Daily</td>\r\n			<td>PCs and files</td>\r\n			<td>Emails</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Securities (logbooks and title deeds)</td>\r\n			<td>Daily</td>\r\n			<td>PCs and files</td>\r\n			<td>None</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n