<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">4</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"7\"><strong>Audit Process (to delete)</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">1</td>\r\n			<td>Audit Objective</td>\r\n			<td>Initials</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">W/P Ref</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">1a</td>\r\n			<td>Audit Procedure 1</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Audit Procedure 2</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Audit Procedure 3</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Audit Procedure 4</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Audit Procedure 5</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Audit Procedure 6</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">1b</td>\r\n			<td>Audit conclusions</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Etc</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<h1>Annex 7: Audit notification (Form 8.7)</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>INTERNAL AUDIT DEPARTMENT</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>INTERNAL MEMO</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>TO:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>(Name of the Auditee)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>FROM:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>(Name of the auditor)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>REF:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>(Audit reference number)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DATE:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>(Date of memo)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SUBJECT: &nbsp;&nbsp; AUDIT NOTIFICATION</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is to inform you that the internal audit department will be conducting an audit on the</p>\r\n\r\n<p>______________________________________process of your department/branch on ______________________________.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The purpose of this audit is to examine and review the _______________________________ for the period___________________________.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There should be no restriction or limitation on the scope of this audit and in whatsoever circumstances; the internal audit staff shall have unrestricted access to all the records, property and personnel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The audit is scheduled to take approximately ________________weeks/days to complete and should there be any weakness in the process the same will be discussed with you together with our recommendations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order for us to work efficiently as possible, it is understood that your co-operation is greatly appreciated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(Auditor&rsquo;s Name)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Annex 8: Internal Audit Charter</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Purpose</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The purpose of the internal audit charter is to set out the nature, role, responsibility, status and authority of the internal audit department and to outline the scope of the internal audit work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Standards</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Internal Auditor will adhere to the Institute of Internal Auditors&rsquo; &ldquo;Code of Ethics&rdquo;.&nbsp;The Internal Audit Charter is suggested as best practice by the Standards for the Professional Practice of Internal Auditing of the Institute of Internal Auditors, which states that &ldquo;the purpose, authority and responsibility of the internal audit activity should be formally defined in a charter, consistent with the Standards, and approved by the Musoni Kenya Board of Directors. In addition, IA staff will adhere to operating procedures as described in Musoni standard operating policies and procedures manuals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reporting Line</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Musoni Kenya Internal Auditor reports to the CEO and the chairman of the Audit Committee of Musoni Kenya.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Authority Granted to Internal Audit</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Musoni Kenya Internal Auditor has full, free, and unrestricted access to all levels of management, the records (manual and electronic), properties, and personnel of Musoni.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The internal auditor has always access to the chair of the Musoni Kenya Audit committee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Responsibility of Internal Audit</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Internal Audit is responsible for developing and maintaining an efficient and effective programme of internal auditing to enhance Musoni&rsquo;s capacity to manage risk and assure the Musoni Kenya Board of Directors that the systems of internal control are designed to achieve the objectives of Musoni.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Scope of Work and assurance tasks</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The scope of internal auditing encompasses, but is not limited to, the examination and evaluation of the adequacy and effectiveness of the organization&#39;s governance, risk management, and internal process as well as the quality of performance in carrying out assigned responsibilities to achieve the organisation&rsquo;s stated goals and objectives. This includes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Checking Musoni&rsquo;s approved procedures, processes and transactions to ascertain if they are being followed using the Musoni manuals as a basis to perform these checks.</li>\r\n	<li>Evaluate Musoni internal control systems established to ensure compliance with Musoni policies, procedures, and guidelines</li>\r\n	<li>Carry out any specific audit requests or investigation</li>\r\n	<li>Evaluate the validity, accuracy and completeness of documentation and other information as regards financial, accounting, administrative, managerial and the operational functions of Musoni</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that booking are made timely, accurately, and completely</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinate the work of Internal Auditors with the external auditors.</li>\r\n	<li>Freely plan and direct the work in consultation with management through a constructive working relationship with them and with the Musoni Audit Committee.</li>\r\n	<li>Identify and report to the management actual and potential weakness in the systems of internal control where it exists, and recommend feasible ways to remedy it.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The audit charter shall be approved by the Audit Committee and subsequently ratified by the board as part of their supervisory role before the start of each financial year. The Audit Committee shall review the audit charter at least once every year</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Annex 9; Budgeted versus the audit plan format</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table style=\"width:595px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>#</td>\r\n			<td>Audit Area/Item</td>\r\n			<td>Office Location</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">Budgeted days</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">Actual Days</td>\r\n			<td>Audit Comment</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td><strong>HIA</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>IA</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>AIA</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>HIA</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>IA</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>AIA</strong></td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Branch A</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Branch B</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Branch C</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;4</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>Finance</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>5</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>HR</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>6</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>IT</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;